						<div class="postbody">malloc's argument is always in bytes... at least, on all machines that I've ever used that have bytes as an available primitive.<br /><br />You might like calloc, for that purpose, because its two arguments are &quot;how many&quot; and &quot;of what size&quot; (i.e. &quot;sizeof unsigned short&quot; here)</div>

